Anonymous Sun 03 Feb 2019 16:46:45 No.21070769 Report
Quoted By:
>>21070063
You go from present to past tense half way through the story ('says' turns into 'said'), and on the 16th line you go from second to first person. Pick a tense and a perspective and stick to it.
It could do with a quick proof-reading so you can add in some missing words here and there
Mention how your characters feel some more. When Anon is pulling his wolverine waifu away from the guy, is he feeling embarrassed? Is he angry with Scratch? Is he casual about the situation because it's happened so many times? Be sure to tell your audience.
You use 'he/she said as' a lot to transition from dialogue to action. Try to mix it up a little (I'm a bit guilty of this in the stuff I write, too).
Maybe be a little more subtle with the her emotions. going from angry to stammering like shit because your bf wants to hold hands is one hell of a change in such a short time (Admittedly this one is more personal preference).
Overall it's not bad for a first try. Keep going mane, you'll get better with time.

Also wolverines are just black honey badgers.
